548	/// Print the full bench report: header line (logfmt-style metadata),
549	/// per-band histogram, whole-histogram mean/stdev, and trimmed
550	/// mean/stdev (every band below the n2 ≡ p99 tail cut). The trimmed
551	/// rows are labeled by the span of populated non-tail bands (e.g.
552	/// `mean z4..n2`), so `min` — never a row — is not asserted and an
553	/// empty n2 band is not named; see the label derivation below.
554	///
555	/// Each histogram row is one band, labeled by its **upper**
556	/// boundary — deciles in the body (`p10` … `p90`), nines/zeros in
557	/// the tails (`zK`/`nK` = fraction 10^-K of samples below/above
558	/// the boundary) — the lower boundary being the previous printed
559	/// row (empty bands are skipped). Bands are **right-closed**
560	/// `(lower, upper]` (see [`band_index`]): a sample whose rank lands
561	/// exactly on a boundary counts in the band that boundary caps, so a
562	/// lone median sample reads `p50`, not `p60` — matching the
563	/// upper-boundary label and the CDF definition of a percentile. This
564	/// is `pandas.cut`'s `right=True` convention; the rank is the Hazen
565	/// plotting position `(i - 0.5) / n`. Label style comes from
566	/// `cfg.band_labels` and is recorded as `labels=` in the header
567	/// metadata so saved outputs are self-describing. The `adjusted`
568	/// columns subtract per-call apparatus overhead
569	/// (`cfg.overhead.adjust_per_call_ns(inner)` — the amortized loop
570	/// cost plus the dithered in-interval framing slice amortized by
571	/// `inner`); the untrimmed `stdev` is the
572	/// hdrhistogram-native stdev, which includes the ms-scale outliers
573	/// in the tail band. Ends with `WARNING` lines flagging poisoned
574	/// stats when they apply — `suspended_s` comes from
575	/// [`run_adaptive`] (see [`warn_invalid`]).
576	#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]
577	// OK: 8th arg tipped the lint; folding the run outputs into a
578	// struct is the probe-based harness rework (todo), not a
579	// side-effect of this change.
580	pub fn print_report(
581	    name: &str,
582	    outer: u64,
583	    inner: u64,
